Notebook[{
Cell["FindOrthogonalFrame", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"81a65855-ca22-4fd7-b499-cffec09aae80"],

Cell["[LLM Generated]", "Subtitle",ExpressionUUID->"f7f20e0e-e2c0-4238-bcaa-cec7497c0569"],

Cell["\<\
FindOrthogonalFrame[g, c, axisLength] returns one orthogonal frame at centre \
c with each axis half-depth constrained by axisLength (All | n_Integer | \
UpTo[n] | {min, max}): a list of InfraSegment axes (full metric lines through \
c, c strictly interior), mutually perpendicular at c. FindOrthogonalFrame[g, \
c, axisLength, n] / UpTo[n] / All controls the number of distinct frames. \
Centre is a vertex or InfraPoint[{c1, \[Ellipsis], ck}]. Options: Method \
(Automatic = \"Exhaustive\", or \"Greedy\"), \"AxisCount\" (Automatic | k | \
UpTo[k] | All), \"BranchSampleSize\", \"SelectCoordinate\". For the no-centre \
form use FindSpanningAxes.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"100f96a3-16d2-4cae-8d28-9ee86dce9b09"],

Cell["Setup", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"3b76685b-0b0d-4bbc-b909-2d12c7639d6d"],

Cell["Load the paclet.", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"37fa2652-63df-4dad-ae74-46a955ab9582"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"Needs", "[", "\"\<WolframInstitute`SyntheticInfrageometry`\>\"", 
  "]"}]], "Code",
 InitializationCell->
  True,ExpressionUUID->"592b12e1-d08d-4e3f-b6fe-6a1e1ff00890"],

